<div class="eight wide column">
  <%= yield %>

  <h3><b>What is Tcal?</b></h3>
  <ul class="main-points">
    <li>Tcal <b>is not</b> another phone app.</li>
    <li>Tcal <b>is</b> a service which makes <b>your timetable</b> available in Google Calendar.</li>
    <li>Tcal keeps time and module <b>changes in sync</b>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3><b>What's the point?</b></h3>
  <ul class="main-points">
    <li><b>iPhone</b> and <b>Android</b> come with a calendar app. Tcal makes use of it.</li>
    <li>Know what you have and where to go, <b>without even unlocking</b> your phone.</li>
    <li>Manage the rest of your busy, personal day/night schedule in your calendar alongside your college timetable.</li>
    <small><li>The MyDay app kinda sucks...</li></small>
  </ul>
</div>

